## Recovery Prompt Validation Checklist

**IMPORTANT**: Before finalizing this recovery prompt, verify all fields are complete.
**Purpose**: Ensure prompt is usable for session resumption (incomplete prompts cause confusion).

### Section 1: Header Information
- [ ] Session ID present (e.g., "Session 5" or "Session_20250111_143000")
- [ ] Git commit hash present (7+ characters) OR version timestamp if no git
- [ ] Context percentage present (0-100)
- [ ] Status present (IN_PROGRESS/COMPLETED/BLOCKED)

### Section 2: Goal
- [ ] Goal description present (what session is accomplishing)
- [ ] Goal is specific (not vague like "work on project")

### Section 3: Completed
- [ ] Completed list present (may be empty for first session)
- [ ] Each item uses ‚úÖ emoji and past tense verb
- [ ] List matches master_state.json modules_complete/sections_complete

### Section 4: In Progress
- [ ] Current task specified (or explicitly state "None")
- [ ] If task present: Uses üîÑ emoji and present continuous tense
- [ ] If task present: Partial work described (what's done, what remains)
- [ ] If task present: Next steps listed for resuming (minimum 1 step)

### Section 5: Next Steps
- [ ] Next steps list present (minimum 1 item)
- [ ] Steps are actionable (start with verb: "Read", "Implement", "Test", etc.)
- [ ] Steps are ordered (1, 2, 3...)
- [ ] Immediate next step clearly identified

### Section 6: Context Needed
- [ ] Files needed for resumption listed
- [ ] Each file has brief reason ("Why needed")
- [ ] State files included (master_state.json at minimum)

### Section 7: Recovery Prompt (Paste This)
- [ ] Recovery prompt block present (the ```...``` section)
- [ ] Prompt mentions this recovery file by name
- [ ] Prompt includes git commit hash (or version)
- [ ] Prompt has specific instructions (not just "continue work")
- [ ] Prompt specifies autonomous mode status (ACTIVE/INACTIVE)
- [ ] Prompt reminds about 35% context target

### Section 8: Files Modified
- [ ] All modified files listed
- [ ] Each file has description of changes
- [ ] List is accurate (matches git diff or actual changes)

### Section 9: Important Notes
- [ ] If blockers exist: Documented here
- [ ] If edge case occurred: Documented here
- [ ] If emergency stop: INCOMPLETE flag present

### Section 10: Session Metrics
- [ ] Duration present (minutes)
- [ ] Context percentage present (final value)
- [ ] Files modified count present
- [ ] Commits count present
- [ ] Tests status present (if applicable to project type)

